reviews.review: I love it and waiting for a new star wars saga.

A solid film with plenty of fan service that made it feel more like a true SW film.  Had most of the early parts of this film and notes touched on by JJ Abrams been laid out by Rian Johnson in TLJ, the complaints about this film would be eliminated.  He stuck the landing with this film the best he could with the lack of material and vision from the prior director.
I have enjoyed the Star Wars saga and was entertained by The Rise of SKYWALKER. It wrapped up the saga in a delightful way. Action throughout and call backs to old characters and themes.

I loved The Last Jedi, though I wish some things would've been done differently. Rise of Skywalker is absolutely perfect in that it takes everything from VII and VIII and makes it all make sense and gives a brilliant ending to the trilogy. Specifically, it fixes every issue I had with The Last Jedi. 

This movie is amazing and is a culmination of 9 movies worth of storytelling and also is a love letter to fans of Star Wars.
I loved it and thought it was a great finale for Star Wars.
terrible pacing, retconning of 8 previous films, narrative doesnt make sense, more mystery boxes opened than closed.

It was great, it was fun. Star wars is supposed to be entertaining and fun. I mean the Last Jedi was horiawful. this cleaned up a lot of that mess. Critics are useless i agree with them maybe 10% or less on movies i see. They judge movies way to much with political or ideological issues in mind. They also have too much influence on something like rotten tomatoes......my advice to others is look what the audience score was not the critics score was.
Favorite movie of the current series. Abrams righted the ship!

Way too many plot holes left open. Backtracking is all over this movie. Too many fan service moments that will make you cringe, this is coming from a die-hard fan of the series. The movie can't decide which direction it wants to go in ever so it tries to please everyone while simultaneously pleasing nobody
Life long Star Wars fan! The only wish I had was for the Last Jedi to have been directed by JJ so Rise had more time to layout the entire plot
